<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1083" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1083">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Hutchinson</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-08-08"><hi rend="italic">August 8,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hutchinson states that the Bermudez Company manager files formal
                            protest with the legation of the United States. He claims absolute
                            denial of justice.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>